    .recipe-container
      h1.recipe-title Chicken Tikka Masala Recipe
      p.recipe-text A classic Indian dish with marinated chicken cooked in a creamy tomato-based sauce.

      h2.ingredients-title Ingredients
      ul.ingredient-list
        li 500g boneless chicken, cut into pieces
        li 1 cup plain yogurt
        li 2 onions, finely chopped
        li 2 tomatoes, pureed
        li 1/4 cup heavy cream
        li 1/4 cup butter
        li 1 tbsp ginger-garlic paste
        li 1 tsp cumin powder
        li 1 tsp coriander powder
        li 1/2 tsp turmeric powder
        li 1/2 tsp red chili powder
        li 1/2 tsp garam masala
        li 1/4 tsp cinnamon powder
        li Salt to taste

      h2.procedure-title Procedure
      p.procedure-step Marinate the chicken with yogurt, ginger-garlic paste, cumin powder, coriander powder, turmeric powder, red chili powder, and salt. Refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
      p.procedure-step Grill or cook the marinated chicken until fully cooked and slightly charred.
      p.procedure-step In a pan, melt butter and saut√© chopped onions until golden brown.
      p.procedure-step Add tomato puree and cook until the oil separates.
      p.procedure-step Add cumin powder, coriander powder, cinnamon powder, and garam masala. Cook for a couple of minutes.
      p.procedure-step Reduce the heat and stir in the cream.
      p.procedure-step Add the grilled chicken pieces and simmer for a few minutes.
      p.procedure-step Garnish with cilantro and serve the delicious Chicken Tikka Masala with naan or rice.

    

